Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @Leek{1}. Halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

Chop the @Irish Pork Sausages{225%grams} into 2cm wide slices.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

== Sauce ==

Pop the @Passata{1%pack} into a #small bowl{}.

Add @Sugar{1%tbsp} (double for 4p), @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}.

Mix well to combine. You've made your base sauce!

== Filling ==

Heat a drizzle of @Oil{to taste} in a #large pan{} on medium-high heat.

When the oil is hot add the sausages and cook for ~{3-4%mins}, stirring occasionally. Remove from the pan when cooked through.

> IMPORTANT: The sausages are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Return the (now empty) pan to the heat and add another drizzle of oil, if necessary.

Once hot, add the leek and season with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}. Cook until softened, ~{4-6%mins}, stirring occasionally.

== Assembly ==

Divide the sauce between the @Flatbread{2}. Use a #spoon{} to spread the sauce over the base, leaving a 1cm border around the edge (as the crust).

Scatter the @Grated Cheese{50%grams} mix over the flatbreads.

Top with the sausage and leek, spreading everything out evenly.

Carefully pop your flatbreads onto a lined #baking tray{} and bake in your oven until the cheese has melted and is bubbling, ~{6-7%mins}.

== Grated Carrot Salad ==

While the flatbreads bake, trim the @Carrot{1}(trimmed), then coarsely grate (no need to peel).

Mix together the @Balsamic Vinegar{1%sachet} and @Oil{2%tbsp} (double for 4p) to make your dressing.

> Don't do this too early or the salad will become soggy.

Just before serving, toss the @Salad Leaves{40%grams} and grated carrot in the dressing.

Season to taste with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}.

== Serving ==

Remove the flatbread from the oven and cut into slices.

Serve with the salad alongside.